{
  "text": "The natural polyphenolic compound, resveratrol (trans-3,5,4-trihydroxystilbene), is found in peanuts, grapes and a variety of berries, as well as in food products derived from these foods, such as wine [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Resveratrol exhibits a number of beneficial health effects, including anti-inflammatory, anti-oxidant, cardioprotective and anti-tumor properties [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , as well as affecting tumorigenesis and tumor progression [CITATION_5] .",
